body:
**Description**

Use SKTypeface.FromStream() to load a custom font from file, and then call SKFontManager.Default.MatchTypeface() to change the font style, but it returns null.

Based on https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/dotnet/api/skiasharp.skfontmanager.matchtypeface?view=skiasharp-2.88, it should never return null.

**Code**

<!-- a snippet of code that demonstrates the issue -->
    private void OnButtonClick()
    {
        var typeface = GetTypeface("tahoma");

        // Change style to SKFontStyle.Bold or Italic does not matter, all return null
        var modifiedTypeface = SKFontManager.Default.MatchTypeface(typeface, SKFontStyle.Normal);
    }

    private static SKTypeface GetTypeface(string fullFontName)
    {
        SKTypeface result;

        var assembly = Assembly.GetExecutingAssembly();
        var stream = assembly.GetManifestResourceStream($"BlazorCustomFont.{fullFontName}.ttf");
        if (stream == null)
            return null;

        result = SKTypeface.FromStream(stream);
        return result;
    }

**Expected Behavior**

<!-- a general description of what was the expected behavior or result -->
"modifiedTypeface" should return the typeface with modified style.

**Actual Behavior**

<!-- a general description of what really happened -->
"modifiedTypeface" is null

**Basic Information**

- Version with issue:  <!-- the version of SkiaSharp that has the issue --> 2.88.3
- Last known good version:  <!-- the version of SkiaSharp that still working --> n/a
- IDE:  <!-- Visual Studio / Visual Studio for Mac / MonoDevelop / Visual Studio Code --> VS 2022
- Platform Target Frameworks: <!-- all that apply, remove the platforms that aren't broken or haven't had any testing -->
  .net 7 Blazor

<!-- if the issue is a visual issue, please include screenshots showing the problem if possible -->

**Reproduction Link**

<!-- please upload or provide a link to a reproduction case -->
https://github.com/jjzhang12/SkiaCustomFontIssue
